node.title: NSW records 38,625 COVID-19 cases, 11 deaths
node.alt: a healthcare worker conducting a swab to a person in a car
node.description: NSW records more infections in the past three days than the entirety of the Delta outbreak, between June 16 until November 29 when the Omicron strain was first detected.Â
node.content:
["NSW has recorded 38,625 COVID-19 cases and 11 deaths in the latest reporting period.\u00a0", "The state has recorded more infections in the past three days than the entirety of the Delta outbreak, between June 16 until November 29 when the Omicron strain was first detected.\u00a0", "Hospitalisations in the state have\u00a0grown exponentially with another 129 patients admitted for COVID treatment, bringing the total to 1,738.\u00a0", "Premier Dominic Perrottet has previously stated the government's focus would be on intensive care figures, which now stands at 134.\u00a0", "However, NSW Health estimates about 74 per cent of the COVID positive patients admitted to ICU since December 16 were infected with the Delta variant.\u00a0", "Of those patients, 62 per cent were not vaccinated or had received only one dose of a vaccine.\u00a0", "More to come.", "", "
What to do if you're unwell and suspect you have COVID but can't get a test.
